{
  "texts": [
    "Fortunately, AI techniques have great potential to improve performance through system-level design, i.e., the joint design of all blocks in the system.",
    "The system-level design for ISAC is shown in Figure 17, where the ISAC-BS with auto-encoder architecture detects a target and serves K single-antenna users.",
    "At the transmitter, the communication symbols m = [m 1,..., m K] and the prior information of the target Θ are mapped to the transmitted waveform x by a DNN (encoder).",
    "Furthermore, each communication user uses a DNN (decoder) to decode the received signal and a DNN is used by the radar receiver to estimate the sensor parameter θ.",
    "The estimation loss function is defined as the MSE between the ground truth ϑ and the estimated value θ, i.e,J S = ϑ -θ 2."
  ]
}